SmartReno Workflow State Transition Rules

This platform depends on workflow statuses across intake, payment, estimating, RFP, bidding, walkthroughs, and project coordination.

Core rules:

- Never invent new statuses unless explicitly instructed
- Never rename an existing status without inspecting all references first
- Never change workflow progression casually
- Never update a status field without tracing every downstream dependency
- Never assume one status field is the only workflow driver; inspect all related fields first

Before changing any workflow logic:

1. Identify the exact status field(s) involved
2. Search all references across frontend, backend, Edge Functions, and SQL
3. Identify all triggers, automations, notifications, and UI tabs depending on that status
4. Confirm whether transitions are role-dependent
5. Make the smallest possible fix

Critical workflow areas:

- homeowner intake progression
- estimate checkout/payment confirmation
- estimator assignment
- site visit scheduling
- walkthrough completion
- quote generation
- RFP creation
- contractor bid submission
- shortlist/selection logic
- project handoff / completion states

Safety rules:

- Never skip required intermediate statuses to “make the UI work”
- Never backfill statuses blindly
- Never create dual sources of truth for project state
- Never update state in the client if the existing trusted pattern is server-side

When changing workflow logic, always output:

1. root cause
2. exact status fields involved
3. downstream systems affected
4. minimal safe fix
5. manual regression checklist

